lab_values.histopathological examination: confirmed diagnosis of hypertrophic lichen planus characterized by hyperkeratotic, acanthotic squamous epithelium with elongation of the rete ridges and dense bands of lymphohistocytic infiltration in papillary dermis hugging the epidermis

diagnosis: Type II choledochal cyst/double GB/Type VI choledochal cyst

lab_values.ultrasound: hypoechoic lesion located around the porta hepatis with a contracted gall bladder and no intra-hepatic biliary radicle dilatation
lab_values.magnetic resonance cholangiopancreatogra: hypoechoic lesion located around the porta hepatis with a contracted gall bladder and no intra-hepatic biliary radicle dilatation
lab_values.microscopy: papillary hyperplasia of the mucosa with features of chronic inflammation in the wall of the gall bladder
